    {
      "id": "fa18f8a255e8997a4af1ac061167bc60189e1def",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-01-31 19:56:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis seems like a duplicate of patch https://review.whamcloud.com/2102 \"LU-1071 lnet: add config file support for routes and ip2nets params\" which was previously abandoned for a few different reasons. \n\nInstead of adding a new config file to emulate the module parameters, why not use the existing lnetctl YAML config file to configure the routes after startup?  That avoids adding any new lines to the code. If there is a gap in the lnetctl functionality it would be good to understand that and address it rather than going back to modprobe as a mechanism for configuration.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "47c513011bbaddd6a49a3a9fee49c3bb682a1f68",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2021-01-31 20:42:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI agree with Andreas. The solution is the YAML approach. Are you running into an ioctl size limitation when using YAML?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
